 years later, John Noyes died in the same town — at Dartmouth's Mary Hitchcock Memorial Hospital — at age 22.","number":2}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"John Henry Colby","first_name":"John","last_name":"Colby","middle_name":"Henry","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://images.findagrave.com/photos/2013/28/79963985_135950410554.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"john-colby-1862"},"HD2304":{"id":"HD2304","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00729","mother_id":"HD2302"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"label":"Cornelius family genealogy 1904","url":"https://archive.org/details/historyofcorneli00corn/page/n43/mode/2up"}],"gender":"male","marriages":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1893,"month":12,"day":15,"city":"Boston","county":"Suffolk County","state":"Massachusetts"},"death":{"year":1916,"month":12,"day":7,"city":"Hanover","county":"Grafton County","state":"New Hampshire"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM095"},"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST133","institution_blurb":"Boston Latin School class of 1912 — the school's largest senior class to that date (102 members). Award for excellence in modern studies 1908."},{"institution_id":"INST058","institution_blurb":"Dartmouth College class of 1916 (A.B.). Football letter man three years; president Dartmouth College Club and class of '16; Beta Theta Pi."},{"institution_id":"INST133","relationship":"alumnus","years":"class of 1912","institution_blurb":"Attended Boston Latin School (class of 1912)."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"He died eight days before his 23rd birthday","body":"John Noyes Colby graduated from Dartmouth in 1916 — class president, football letter man, Beta Theta Pi. He enrolled in a post-graduate course at the Tuck Hospital in Hanover. In early November he contracted pneumonia, recovered enough to spend Thanksgiving in Boston, returned to Hanover on December 3, relapsed, and died on December 7, 1916 at Mary Hitchcock Memorial Hospital.","number":1},{"header":"Three generations of Dartmouth men","body":"John Noyes Colby entered Dartmouth following his father John Henry Colby (class of 1885) and his grandfather John Freeman Colby (class of 1859). Three consecutive generations of the same family at the same college, each a decade and a half apart. John Noyes graduated in 1916 — the year he died.","number":2},{"header":"Dartmouth president Hopkins called him 'a credit","body":"At John Noyes Colby's funeral on December 10, 1916, Dr. Ernest Hopkins, president of Dartmouth College, represented the faculty and stated: 'a credit to mankind, to his friends and his college, a man to be remembered as a liberalizing influence, whether on the playground, in the fraternity gatherings or in the college classroom.' The church at West Newton Street was full of college students. All pallbearers were from Beta Theta Pi.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"John Noyes Colby","first_name":"John","last_name":"Colby","middle_name":"Noyes","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST133","school_name":"Boston Latin School","dates":"class of 1912","type":"secondary","notes":"Class of 1912; largest class to that date with 102 members; received award for modern languages per research notes."}],"slug":"john-colby-1893"},"HD2303":{"id":"HD2303","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from